/*!
\page string_strstr STRSTR String Search Function

<p>
Section: \ref sec_string "String Functions"
\section Usage
Searches for the first occurance of one string inside another.
The general syntax for its use is
\verbatim
   p = strstr(x,y)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> and <tt>y</tt> are two strings.  The returned integer <tt>p</tt>
indicates the index into the string <tt>x</tt> where the substring <tt>y</tt>
occurs.  If no instance of <tt>y</tt> is found, then <tt>p</tt> is set to
zero.
\section Example
Some examples of <tt>strstr</tt> in action

